Description . Habitus typical of the genus. Body length (without antennae): 0.86–1.45 mm ( holotype : 1.38 mm). Colour of the body bluish grey. 2 + 2 medium dark-pigmented eyes (
Fig. 1
).

Types of dorsal ordinary chaetae. Macrochaetae Ml rather long, thickened, tapered, fusiform, straight or slightly arc-like, narrowly sheathed, feebly serrated, apically rounded or pointed (
Figs 11–12, 18 – 21
); macrochaetae Mc and Mcc thickened, fusiform, straight or slightly arc-like, apically rounded or pointed; mesochaetae and microchaetae short, thin, feebly serrated and pointed.
